## (3)(a) OFDM Advantages and Disadvantages

> OFDM is the modulation technique used by 4G LTE. What are the main advantages and disadvantages related to transmitter and receiver architecture of this technique? *(6 marks)*

---

**Advantages:**

- **Resilience to multipath** - narrow subcarriers experience flat fading, easier to equalize
- **Simple equalization** - single-tap equalizer per subcarrier (just multiply by a coefficient)
- **Spectral efficiency** - subcarriers overlap without interference (orthogonal)
- **Flexible bandwidth** - can use 1.4, 3, 5, 10, 15, or 20 MHz by changing number of subcarriers
- **Efficient implementation** - uses FFT/IFFT algorithms (fast, well-optimized)

**Disadvantages:**

- **High PAPR** - Peak-to-Average Power Ratio requires expensive linear amplifiers
- **Frequency offset sensitivity** - small carrier frequency errors cause inter-carrier interference
- **Strict synchronization** - requires accurate time and frequency sync between TX and RX
- **Cyclic prefix overhead** - wastes some bandwidth to prevent inter-symbol interference

> LTE uses SC-FDMA (not OFDM) for uplink to reduce PAPR and save phone battery.

