### (ii) Advantages of Relay Nodes

> Explain the advantages of relay nodes in Heterogeneous Networks? *(7 marks)*

**What is a Relay Node?**

A relay node (RN) is a low-power base station that connects to the core network **wirelessly** through a donor eNB, rather than via wired backhaul.

---

**Advantages:**

- **Extend coverage** - fills holes at cell edges, indoors, and shadow areas
- **No wired backhaul needed** - uses wireless link to donor eNB, reducing deployment cost
- **Quick deployment** - can be installed rapidly without fiber installation
- **Lower cost** - cheaper than deploying a full eNB with fiber
- **Capacity boost** - offloads traffic from macro cell in hotspot areas
- **Improved cell-edge performance** - users far from macro cell get better signal via relay
- **Flexible placement** - can be mounted on lamp posts, walls, or inside buildings
